<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCD6A72FCEA97821AC3B86F" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCD6A72FCEA97821AC3B86F" blockId="54.[789,1382,396,823]" lastBlockId="54.[162,1380,828,2005]" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">
The relationship with congeners is uncertain but the species seems to be closely related to either 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FC1094731A56B979" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[1004,1110,554,587]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FB7594731B04B979" authorityName="A. B. Meyer" authorityYear="1899" box="[1161,1284,554,587]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="petersi">H. petersi</taxonomicName>
, based on limited genetic data. Specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCD6A72FCEA94201D9BB9A8" box="[790,923,633,666]" name="Myanmar" pageId="54" pageNumber="812">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
that were previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FCEA94FD1D82B9F3" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[790,898,676,705]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
under the name austenianus are now considered to represent this species, although the specimens from Meghalaya that were included under the same name may represent either this species, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCD6A72FD7195651CF5B86F" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[653,757,828,861]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="812" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
, or a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
